{
 "name": "docs-chatbot: 1. ingest documents",
 "nodes": [
  {
   "id": "c1000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000001",
   "name": "Read me first",
   "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
   "typeVersion": 1,
   "position": [
    180,
    120
   ],
   "parameters": {
    "content": "## docs-chatbot ingest\nUpload files here, they get chunked, embedded and stored in Supabase.\n\nBefore first run:\n1. Run supabase-setup.sql in your Supabase project (SQL editor)\n2. Attach a Supabase credential to the vector store node (project URL + service_role key, both under Project Settings > API)\n3. Attach your free Gemini API key to the embeddings node\n\nThen open the form URL from the trigger node, upload your .md/.txt/.pdf files and submit. Re-running with the same files creates duplicates, clear the documents table first if you re-ingest.",
    "width": 400,
    "height": 320,
    "color": 4
   }
  },
  {
   "id": "c1000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000002",
   "name": "Upload form",
   "type": "n8n-nodes-base.formTrigger",
   "typeVersion": 2.2,
   "position": [
    640,
    300
   ],
   "webhookId": "c1000000-0000-4000-8000-00000000f001",
   "parameters": {
    "formTitle": "Add documents to the chatbot",
    "formDescription": "Upload the files the bot should know. Markdown, text or PDF.",
    "formFields": {
     "values": [
      {
       "fieldLabel": "Documents",
       "fieldType": "file",
       "multipleFiles": true,
       "acceptFileTypes": ".md,.txt,.pdf",
       "requiredField": true
      }
     ]
    },
    "options": {}
   }
  },
  {
   "id": "c1000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000003",
   "name": "Store in Supabase",
   "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.vectorStoreSupabase",
   "typeVersion": 1.1,
   "position": [
    920,
    300
   ],
   "parameters": {
    "mode": "insert",
    "tableName": {
     "__rl": true,
     "value": "documents",
     "mode": "list",
     "cachedResultName": "documents"
    },
    "options": {
     "queryName": "match_documents"
    }
   }
  },
  {
   "id": "c1000000-0000-4000-8000-000000000004",
   "name": "Load files",
